In [4]:
def extraer_dominio(texto):
    palabras = texto.split()
    for palabra in palabras:
        if '.' in palabra:
            return palabra

    return None

df['capacity'] = df['capacity'].str.replace(',','')
df['capacity'] = df['capacity'].str.replace('+','')

df['capacidad_numero'] = pd.to_numeric(df['capacidad_numero'].str.split(' ').str[0], errors='coerce')


df['tipo_venue'] = df['tipo_venue'].str.extract(r'\((.*?)\)')

In [49]:
def clean_country(row):
    if pd.isna(row['country']):
        return row['location']
    elif row['country'].endswith('USA'):
        return 'USA'
    elif row['country'] == 'Singapore. Singapore':
        return  'Singapore'
    else:
        return row['country']

In [67]:
continent_dict = {
    'AF': 'Africa',
    'AS': 'Asia',
    'EU': 'Europe',
    'NA': 'North America',
    'OC': 'Oceania',
    'SA': 'South America'
}

def get_continent(country_name):
    try:
        country = pycountry.countries.get(name=country_name)
        if not country:
            country = pycountry.countries.search_fuzzy(country_name)[0]
        country_alpha2 = country.alpha_2
        continent_code = pc.country_alpha2_to_continent_code(country_alpha2)
        return continent_dict[continent_code]
    except Exception as e:
        return None
    

df['continent'] = df['country'].apply(get_continent)

In [112]:
additional_stopwords = {'will', 's', 'Ltd', 'etc','club','7JQ','year'}

def create_wordclouds_by_continent(df):
    continents = df['continent'].unique()
    
    for continent in continents:
        # Filter top clubs for the continent
        continent_df = df[df['continent'] == continent]
        
        # Combine all text into one string for the word cloud
        combined_text = ' '.join(continent_df['text'].dropna())
        
        # Create the word cloud with stopwords
        stopwords = set(STOPWORDS)
        stopwords.update(additional_stopwords)
        wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', stopwords=stopwords).generate(combined_text)
        
        # Display the word cloud
        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
        plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
        plt.title(f'Clubs Word Cloud - {continent}')
        plt.axis('off')
        plt.show()

def create_wordcloud_top_10(df):
    top_10 = df.nsmallest(10, 'Rank')
    
    # Combine all text into one string for the word cloud
    combined_text = ' '.join(top_10['text'].dropna())
    
    # Create the word cloud with stopwords
    stopwords = set(STOPWORDS)
    stopwords.update(additional_stopwords)
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', stopwords=stopwords).generate(combined_text)
    
    # Display the word cloud
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.title('Top 10 Clubs Word Cloud')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

In [128]:
def averageplot(column, bycolumn , location_stats):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=column, y=bycolumn, data=location_stats)
    plt.title(f'Average {bycolumn} by {column}')
    plt.xlabel(column)
    plt.ylabel(f'Average {bycolumn}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()



def relationship(column):
    location_stats = df.groupby(column).agg({
    'capacity': 'mean',
    'Rank': 'mean',
    'Club_Name': 'count'
}).reset_index()

    location_stats = location_stats[location_stats['Club_Name'] > 1]

    averageplot(column, 'capacity', location_stats)
    averageplot(column, 'Rank', location_stats)

Observing the data, it appears that clubs with smaller average capacities tend to have better rankings. However, to validate this observation, let's conduct further analysis

In [139]:
correlation_matrix = df[['capacity', 'Rank']].corr()
correlation_matrix
Out[139]:
capacity Rank
capacity 1.000000 -0.315137
Rank -0.315137 1.000000

The correlation matrix shows that there is a moderate negative correlation (r = -0.315137) between the capacity of nightclubs and their ranking. This indicates that, on average, as the capacity of a nightclub decreases, its ranking tends to improve. A negative correlation of this magnitude suggests that smaller-capacity clubs may indeed perform better in terms of ranking, although other factors could also influence this relationship. Further analysis could explore additional variables to better understand the factors affecting nightclub rankings
